              "width": "fill_container",
              "height": 16
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "dAbwH",
              "name": "Article Body",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": "$gap-md",
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "yctuP",
                  "name": "bodyP1",
                  "fill": "$muted-fg",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "TanStack Start is a modern full-stack React framework that brings together the best of server-side rendering and client-side interactivity. In this post, I'll walk through how I built this very blog using TanStack Start, file-based routing, and server functions.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.625,
                  "fontFamily": "DM Sans",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "AA1eZ",
                  "name": "bodyH2",
                  "fill": "$fg",
                  "content": "Why TanStack Start?",
                  "fontFamily": "Space Grotesk",
                  "fontSize": 18,
                  "fontWeight": "700"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "vzYu5",
                  "name": "bodyP2",
                  "fill": "$muted-fg",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "After years of working with Next.js, I wanted to explore alternatives that offered a different approach to server-side rendering while maintaining excellent developer experience. TanStack Start stood out for its type-safe routing and elegant data loading patterns.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.625,
                  "fontFamily": "DM Sans",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "Ev2p8",
                  "name": "bodyH3",
                  "fill": "$fg",
                  "content": "Setting Up the Project",
                  "fontFamily": "Space Grotesk",
                  "fontSize": 18,
                  "fontWeight": "700"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "FZ33G",
                  "name": "bodyP3",
                  "fill": "$muted-fg",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Getting started is straightforward. First, create a new TanStack Start project:",
                  "lineHeight": 1.625,
                  "fontFamily": "DM Sans",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "1CWXn",
                  "name": "Code Block",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "fill": "$muted",
                  "cornerRadius": 8,
                  "stroke": {
                    "align": "inside",
                    "thickness": 1,
                    "fill": "$border"
                  },
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 4,
                  "padding": 16,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "6AtRl",
                      "name": "codeLine1",
                      "fill": "#A6E22E",
                      "content": "npx create-tanstack-app my-blog",
                      "fontFamily": "JetBrains Mono",
                      "fontSize": 12,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "mILOw",
                      "name": "codeLine2",
                      "fill": "#A6E22E",
                      "content": "cd my-blog",
                      "fontFamily": "JetBrains Mono",
                      "fontSize": 12,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "TneWP",
                      "name": "codeLine3",
                      "fill": "#A6E22E",
                      "content": "npm install",
                      "fontFamily": "JetBrains Mono",
                      "fontSize": 12,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "gqSzS",
                  "name": "bodyP4",
                  "fill": "$muted-fg",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "The file-based routing system automatically generates routes from your file structure inside the src/routes/ directory. Each file becomes a route, and dynamic segments use the $param syntax.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.625,
                  "fontFamily": "DM Sans",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "CbY0S",
                  "name": "bodyP5",
                  "fill": "$muted-fg",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Server functions are defined using createServerFn from TanStack Start, providing type-safe RPC between client and server. This is perfect for loading blog post data from the filesystem.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.625,
                  "fontFamily": "DM Sans",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
